\b 1.What is difference between Tag and Element in HTML?\b0\par
\par
 \tab In HTML, an element is a fundamental building block, representing a structure or content piece, while a tag is the specific syntax used to define or mark up that element. For example, `<p>` is a tag that defines a paragraph element. So, `<p>This is a paragraph.</p>` where `<p>` is the opening tag and `</p>` is the closing tag, and the content in between constitutes the element.\par
\par
\par
\b 2. Which are void elements in HTML?\b0\par
\par
\tab Void elements in HTML are those that don't have a closing tag. They self-close or terminate within the opening tag. Examples include `<br>` for line breaks and `<img>` for images. For instance, `<img src="example.jpg" alt="Example Image"/>` is a void element, where the tag doesn't have a separate closing tag.\par
\par
\par
\b 3. What is semantic code in HTML?\b0\par
\par
\tab Semantic code in HTML refers to using tags that convey meaning about the structure and content of a webpage, aiding both browsers and developers in understanding the information. Examples include `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<nav>`, and `<article>`. Semantic code improves accessibility and search engine optimization by providing clear context to the document structure.\par
\par
\par
\par
\b 4. What is the difference between pseudo class and pseudo elements in CSS?\b0\par
\par
\tab In CSS, a pseudo-class is used to select and style a specific state or condition of an element, such as `:hover` or `:focus`. \par
\tab A pseudo-element, on the other hand, selects and styles a part of an element, like `::before` or `::after`. \par
\tab For example, `a:hover` is a pseudo-class targeting the hover state of a link, while `p::first-line` is a pseudo-element styling the first line of a paragraph.\par
\par
\par
\b 5. Where in an HTML document is the correct place to refer to an external style sheet?\b0\par
\par
\tab The correct place to refer to an external style sheet in an HTML document is within the `<head>` section:\par
\par
<!DOCTYPE html>\par
<html>\par
<head>\par
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">\par
</head>\par
<body>\par
  <!-- Content of the webpage -->\par
</body>\par
</html>\par
\par
\par
\par
\b 6. Which HTML tag is used to define an internal style sheet?\b0\par
\par
\tab The HTML `<style>` tag is used to define an internal style sheet. It is placed within the `<head>` section of the HTML document. \par
\par
<!DOCTYPE html>\par
<html>\par
<head>\par
  <style>\par
    body \{\par
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\par
      background-color: #f0f0f0;\par
    \}\par
    h1 \{\par
      color: blue;\par
    \}\par
  </style>\par
</head>\par
<body>\par
  <h1>This is a heading</h1>\par
  <p>This is a paragraph.</p>\par
</body>\par
</html>\par
\par
\par
\par
\b 7. Which HTML attribute is used to define inline styles?\b0\par
\par
\tab The HTML `style` attribute is used to define inline styles. You can add the `style` attribute directly to an HTML element and specify CSS styles within it. \par
  <p style="color: red; font-size: 16px;">This is a paragraph with inline styles.</p>\par
\par
\par
\b\par
8. How do you insert a comment in a CSS file?\par
\b0\par
\tab In CSS, you can insert comments using `/* */`. Anything between these comment delimiters will be ignored by the browser. \par
\par
/* This is a CSS comment */\par
/* Another comment */\par
h1 \{\par
  color: blue;\par
\}\par
\par
\par
\par
\b\par
9. Which property is used to change the background color?\par
\b0\par
\tab The `background-color` property is used to change the background color of an element in CSS. \par
\par
div \{\par
  background-color: lightblue; \par
\}\par
\par
\par
\b 10. How do you add a background color for all <h1> elements?\b0\par
\tab\par
\tab To add a background color for all `<h1>` elements, you can use the `background-color` property in your CSS and target the `<h1>` selector. \par
\par
h1 \{\par
  background-color: #ffcc00; \par
  color: #333; \par
\}\par
\par
\par
\b\par
11. Which CSS property controls the text size?\par
\b0\par
The CSS property that controls the text size is `font-size`. \par
\par
p \{\par
  font-size: 16px;\par
\}\par
\par
\par
\par
\b\par
12. How do you display hyperlinks without an underline?\par
\b0\par
\tab To display hyperlinks without an underline, you can use the `text-decoration` property in CSS and set it to `none` for the `<a>`  selector. \par
\par
a \{\par
  text-decoration: none;\par
\}\par
\par
\par
\par
\b 13. How do you make each word in a text start with a capital letter?\b0\par
\par
\tab You can use the `text-transform` property in CSS and set it to `capitalize` to make each word in a text start with a capital letter.\par
\par
p \{\par
  text-transform: capitalize;\par
\}\par
\par
\par
\par
\par
