15. When using the padding property; are you allowed to use negative values?\par
\b0\par
\tab No, in CSS, we are not allowed to use negative values for the `padding` property. The `padding` property sets the space between the content of an element and its border. It only accepts non-negative values. Attempting to use a negative value for `padding` will not produce the desired effect and is not valid according to the CSS specifications.\par
\par
