\b 17. What is the default value of the position property?\par
\b0\par
\tab The default value of the CSS `position` property is `static`. When an element's position property is set to `static`, it is positioned according to the normal flow of the document, and other positioning properties like `top`, `right`, `bottom`, and `left` have no effect on it.\par
\par
\par
\b 18. How you can define pseudo element?\par
\b0\par
\tab Pseudo-elements in CSS are denoted by a double colon `::` followed by the name of the pseudo-element.\par
\par
p::first-line \{\par
  font-weight: bold;\par
  color: blue;\par
\}\par
\par
\par
